name: 2-phenoxypropionic acid

The phenoxy group (C6H4OH) adds significant bulk and polarity, which can increase the melting point due to stronger intermolecular forces. The carboxylic acid group (COOH) adds to the melting point due to its electronegativity and polarizability, which can increase the melting point.
